\begin_layout Standard
The dynamic pressure is the pressure difference above ambient that develops
 if air is compressed and adiabatically brought to rest relative to the
 moving aircraft.
 The total pressure, the sum of ambient and dynamic pressure, is sensed
 using a pitot tube, a tube pointed in the direction of the relative airflow
